CatDescriptText: The broadside hanging on back wall reads, "Dancing American Legion, 215 Boundary Ave. Clairton, music by, The Four Corners Stompers, Joe Moorefield Piano, Gus[?]Kay Sax, Joey Jackson Guitar, Jimmy Southers Drummer, Shirley Jackson Shake Dancer, Sun. Feb. 22, 1953, 10 - 2 A M, Held By Helping Hand Club, Advance $1.00, At Door, $1.25"
TitMainTitle: Two musicians, one playing drums, the other playing piano, with maracas on top of piano, in club with "gentlemen please remove your hats" sign
